TEACHER.observations: I have been pondering about something: the more I try to communicate (i.e., more gestures and shapes), the more confusing it becomes and the less my partner understands. When I, instead, do the least possible (albeit being clear) it helps to communicate better. I wonder if this is a general trend in the experiment or particular to our game.
